PRINCESS THERESA OWANA KAOHELELANI, etc., Appellant, v. BISHOP TRUST COMPANY, Limited, a Hawaiian Corporation, Appellee. No. 6749. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 20, 1932. M. Louo Heen, of Honolulu, Hawaii, for appellant. Robertson & Castle, of Honolulu, Hawaii, for appellee.

Before WILBUR, Circuit Judge, and JAMES and NORCROSS, District Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal herein dismissed for noneompliance by appellant with the provisions of rules 23 and 24 of the Rules of Practice of this court.
